.TH OMNI 1 "March 2026" "Omni 0.1.5" "Omni Lisp Tools"
.SH NAME
omni \- Omni Lisp CLI, REPL, and project tooling
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B omni
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fIscript.omni\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B omni
starts the Omni Lisp REPL, runs scripts, executes test suites, scaffolds new
projects, and generates FFI bindings.
.PP
When run with no arguments,
.B omni
starts the REPL.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --repl
Start the REPL explicitly.
.TP
.B --repl --json
Start a structured JSON request/response REPL transport for tools.
.TP
.BI --eval " <expr> " "[--json]"
Evaluate one Omni expression supplied on the command line.
Use
.B --json
to emit a structured result payload.
.TP
.BI --check " <file> " "[--json]"
Parse/check an Omni source file without executing it.
Use
.B --json
to emit structured diagnostics with 0-based ranges.
.TP
.BI --test-suite " <all|stack|scope|lisp>"
Run one bundled test suite.
.TP
.BI --build " <file> " "[-o output]"
AOT compile an Omni source file to a standalone executable.
.TP
.BI --compile " <file> <out.c3>"
Compile Omni source to C3 output.
.TP
.BI --init " <name>"
Scaffold a new Omni project directory.
.TP
.BI --bind " [project-dir]"
Generate FFI bindings from
.I omni.toml
for a project directory.
.TP
.B --gen-e2e
Generate end-to-end compiler tests.
.TP
.B --language-ref, --lang-ref, --manual
Print the built-in full language reference bundled in the executable.
.TP
.B --stack-affinity-probe
Run stack ownership fail-fast probe.
.TP
.B -v, --version
Print CLI version.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Print help text.
.SH PROJECT COMMANDS
.SS Init
.EX
omni --init myproject
cd myproject
.EE
.SS Bind
.EX
omni --bind
omni --bind /path/to/project
.EE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run script:
.EX
omni script.omni
.EE
.TP
Evaluate one expression:
.EX
omni --eval '(+ 1 2)'
omni --eval --json '(+ 1 2)'
.EE
.TP
Structured REPL transport:
.EX
printf '%s\n' '{"id":"1","input":"(+ 1 2)","mode":"expr"}' | omni --repl --json
.EE
.TP
Check without executing:
.EX
omni --check app.omni
omni --check --json app.omni
.EE
.TP
Compile to executable:
.EX
omni --build app.omni -o app
.EE
.TP
Compile to C3:
.EX
omni --compile app.omni app.c3
.EE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I omni.toml
Project tooling config used by
.B --bind
\&.
.TP
.I src/main.omni
Default entrypoint created by
.B --init
\&.
.TP
.I docs/PROJECT_TOOLING.md
Detailed project tooling guide.
.SH INSTALLATION
Repository install helper:
.EX
scripts/install_omni.sh install
scripts/install_omni.sh uninstall
.EE
The helper installs:
.IP "\(bu" 2
launcher:
.I <prefix>/bin/omni
.IP "\(bu" 2
binary:
.I <prefix>/lib/omni/omni-bin
.IP "\(bu" 2
man page:
.I <prefix>/share/man/man1/omni.1
.IP "\(bu" 2
language reference:
.I <prefix>/share/man/man7/omni-language.7
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR omni-language (7),
.BR docs/LANGUAGE_SPEC.md ,
.BR docs/PROJECT_TOOLING.md
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
non-zero
CLI, parse, runtime, or tooling failure.
